species
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="663E369ADD205A09FF7AFE7ACF16CC5B" blockId="34.[227,1436,468,530]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD205A09FF7AFE7ACE46CFA5" authority="Gmelin, 1791" authorityName="Gmelin" authorityYear="1791" box="[227,608,468,495]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="leucostictus">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FF7AFE7ACD9BCFA4" box="[227,445,468,495]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Conus leucostictus</emphasis>
Gmelin, 1791
</taxonomicName>
accepted as 
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD205A09FD70FE7AC801CFA5" authority="Gmelin, 1791" authorityName="Gmelin" authorityYear="1791" box="[745,1063,468,495]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="regius">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FD70FE7ACFA7CFA4" box="[745,897,469,495]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Conus regius</emphasis>
Gmelin, 1791
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus id="B93A8838DD205A09FBADFE7AC84ECFA5" box="[1076,1128,469,495]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">type</typeStatus>
by subsequent designation Wenz 1943: 1469). Recent, tropical West Atlantic.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="663E369ADD205A09FF7AFD96CDD1CC19" blockId="34.[227,503,569,595]" box="[227,503,569,595]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<heading id="3D7681F6DD205A09FF7AFD96CDD1CC19" bold="true" box="[227,503,569,595]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" reason="3">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FF7AFD96CDD1CC19" bold="true" box="[227,503,569,595]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Descriptive comments</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="663E369ADD205A09FF7AFDC8CE34CD7B" blockId="34.[226,1436,615,817]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
The nodules on the spire whorls occur on most extant species, except on 
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD205A09FBE6FDC7CE28CCEF" authority="Linnaeus, 1758" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="genuanus" subGenus="Stephanoconus">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FBE6FDC7C8ECCCC8" box="[1151,1226,616,642]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Conus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FB78FDC8C9B5CCCB" box="[1249,1427,615,641]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Stephanoconus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FF7AFD24CD75CCEE" box="[227,339,651,676]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">genuanus</emphasis>
Linnaeus, 1758
</taxonomicName>
and can either fade out or persist in later spire whorls. Some species also have spiral ribs on the body whorl. The protoconch is multispiral. The colour pattern consists of spiral bands (two to three), axial blotches, spiral rows of small to large dots and dashes, in colours of shades brown, cream and white. All 
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD205A09FE70FD5BCF22CD44" authority="" authorityName="Morch" authorityYear="1852" box="[489,772,756,782]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Stephanoconus">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FE70FD5BCE12CD44" box="[489,564,756,782]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Conus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FDD1FD5BCEDCCD44" box="[584,762,756,782]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Stephanoconus</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
feed on Polychaeta have a similar radular morphology (
<bibRefCitation id="02104B6BDD205A09FF73FCB8CE20CD7B" author="Tucker J. K. &amp; Tenorio M. J." box="[234,518,791,817]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" refId="ref32426" refString="Tucker J. K. &amp; Tenorio M. J. 2009. Systematic Classification of Recent and Fossil Conoidean Gastropods: With Keys to the Genera of Cone Shells. ConchBooks, Harxheim." type="book" year="2009">Tucker &amp; Tenorio 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2E9B6511DD205A09FF7AFCF7C8F2C832" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="663E369ADD205A09FF7AFCF7CD73CD38" blockId="34.[227,341,856,882]" box="[227,341,856,882]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<heading id="3D7681F6DD205A09FF7AFCF7CD73CD38" bold="true" box="[227,341,856,882]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" reason="3">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FF7AFCF7CD73CD38" bold="true" box="[227,341,856,882]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="663E369ADD205A09FF7AFC28CF46CA3E" blockId="34.[227,1437,902,1140]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
According to 
<bibRefCitation id="02104B6BDD205A09FE1EFC28CEB9CDEB" author="Puillandre N. &amp; Duda T. F. &amp; Meyer C. &amp; Olivera B. M. &amp; Bouchet P." box="[391,671,902,929]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="1 - 23" refId="ref31531" refString="Puillandre N., Duda T. F., Meyer C., Olivera B. M. &amp; Bouchet P. 2015. One, four or 100 genera? A new classification of the cone snails. The Journal of Molluscan Studies 81 (1): 1 - 23. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / mollus / eyu 055" type="journal article" year="2015">
Puillandre 
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FD93FC28CE1BCDEB" box="[522,573,903,929]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">et al</emphasis>
. (2015)
</bibRefCitation>
, the subgenus occurs in all tropical seas. The phylogenetic trees of 
<bibRefCitation id="02104B6BDD205A09FE9FFC05CDE1CD8E" author="Lin Z. &amp; Torres J. P. &amp; Watkins M. &amp; Paguigan N. &amp; Niu C. &amp; Imperial J. S. &amp; Tun J. &amp; Safavi-Hemami H. &amp; Urdaneta R. K. &amp; Neves J. L. B. &amp; Espino S. &amp; Karthikeyan M. &amp; Olivera B. M. &amp; Schmidt E. W." box="[262,455,938,964]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="685" refId="ref30563" refString="Lin Z., Torres J. P., Watkins M., Paguigan N., Niu C., Imperial J. S., Tun J., Safavi-Hemami H., Finol- Urdaneta R. K., Neves J. L. B., Espino S., Karthikeyan M., Olivera B. M. &amp; Schmidt E. W. 2021. Nonpeptidic small molecule components from cone snail venoms. Frontiers in Pharmacology 12: 685. https: // doi. org / 10.3389 / fphar. 2021.655981" type="journal article" year="2021">
Lin 
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FEA3FC05CD4ACD8E" box="[314,364,938,964]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">et al</emphasis>
. (2021
</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 2) and 
<bibRefCitation id="02104B6BDD205A09FDC3FC05CF1BCD8E" author="Torres J. P. &amp; Lin Z. &amp; Watkins M. &amp; Salcedo P. F. &amp; Baskin R. P. &amp; Elhabian S. &amp; Safavi-Hemami H. &amp; Taylor D. &amp; Tun J. &amp; Concepcion G. P. &amp; Saguil N. &amp; Yanagihara A. A. &amp; Fang Y. &amp; McArthur J. R. &amp; Tae H. - S. &amp; Finol-Urdaneta R. K. &amp; Ozpolat B. D. &amp; Olivera B. M. &amp; Schmidt E. W." box="[602,829,938,964]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="2704" refId="ref32225" refString="Torres J. P., Lin Z., Watkins M., Salcedo P. F., Baskin R. P., Elhabian S., Safavi-Hemami H., Taylor D., Tun J., Concepcion G. P., Saguil N., Yanagihara A. A., Fang Y., McArthur J. R., Tae H. - S., Finol-Urdaneta R. K., Ozpolat B. D., Olivera B. M. &amp; Schmidt E. W. 2021. Small-molecule mimicry hunting strategy in the imperial cone snail, Conus imperialis. Science Advances 7 (11): eabf 2704. https: // doi. org / 10.1126 / sciadv. abf 2704" type="journal article" year="2021">
Torres 
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FD37FC05CEC2CD8E" box="[686,740,938,964]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">et al</emphasis>
. (2021
</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 5), recently found 
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD205A09FBC2FC05CD06CDA2" authority="Linnaeus, 1758" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="genuanus">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FBC2FC05C939CD89" box="[1115,1311,938,964]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Conus genuanus</emphasis>
Linnaeus, 
<quantity id="A1799B7FDD205A09FF7CFC62CD06CDA2" box="[229,288,973,1000]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.46532" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" unit="in" value="1758.0">1758</quantity>
</taxonomicName>
in a clade of 
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FE50FC62CE5FCDAD" box="[457,633,973,999]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Stephanoconus</emphasis>
. This species shares a similar colour pattern with the other species of the subgenus, but lacks nodules on the spire. 
<bibRefCitation id="02104B6BDD205A09FCABFC5FC846CA40" author="Tucker J. K. &amp; Tenorio M. J." box="[818,1120,1008,1034]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" refId="ref32426" refString="Tucker J. K. &amp; Tenorio M. J. 2009. Systematic Classification of Recent and Fossil Conoidean Gastropods: With Keys to the Genera of Cone Shells. ConchBooks, Harxheim." type="book" year="2009">Tucker &amp; Tenorio (2009)</bibRefCitation>
noted that nodules are an important morphological element of this genus and, thus, did not find the connection of 
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD205A09FB42FBBCC9BACA67" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[1243,1436,1043,1069]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="genuanus">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FB42FBBCC9BACA67" box="[1243,1436,1043,1069]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Conus genuanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to other species of this group plausible. Here, we follow 
<bibRefCitation id="02104B6BDD205A09FC09FB99C871CA1A" author="Lin Z. &amp; Torres J. P. &amp; Watkins M. &amp; Paguigan N. &amp; Niu C. &amp; Imperial J. S. &amp; Tun J. &amp; Safavi-Hemami H. &amp; Urdaneta R. K. &amp; Neves J. L. B. &amp; Espino S. &amp; Karthikeyan M. &amp; Olivera B. M. &amp; Schmidt E. W." box="[912,1111,1078,1104]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="685" refId="ref30563" refString="Lin Z., Torres J. P., Watkins M., Paguigan N., Niu C., Imperial J. S., Tun J., Safavi-Hemami H., Finol- Urdaneta R. K., Neves J. L. B., Espino S., Karthikeyan M., Olivera B. M. &amp; Schmidt E. W. 2021. Nonpeptidic small molecule components from cone snail venoms. Frontiers in Pharmacology 12: 685. https: // doi. org / 10.3389 / fphar. 2021.655981" type="journal article" year="2021">
Lin 
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FC5CFB98C824CA1A" box="[965,1026,1078,1104]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">et al.</emphasis>
(2021)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="02104B6BDD205A09FB0DFB98C95ACA1A" author="Torres J. P. &amp; Lin Z. &amp; Watkins M. &amp; Salcedo P. F. &amp; Baskin R. P. &amp; Elhabian S. &amp; Safavi-Hemami H. &amp; Taylor D. &amp; Tun J. &amp; Concepcion G. P. &amp; Saguil N. &amp; Yanagihara A. A. &amp; Fang Y. &amp; McArthur J. R. &amp; Tae H. - S. &amp; Finol-Urdaneta R. K. &amp; Ozpolat B. D. &amp; Olivera B. M. &amp; Schmidt E. W." box="[1172,1404,1078,1105]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="2704" refId="ref32225" refString="Torres J. P., Lin Z., Watkins M., Salcedo P. F., Baskin R. P., Elhabian S., Safavi-Hemami H., Taylor D., Tun J., Concepcion G. P., Saguil N., Yanagihara A. A., Fang Y., McArthur J. R., Tae H. - S., Finol-Urdaneta R. K., Ozpolat B. D., Olivera B. M. &amp; Schmidt E. W. 2021. Small-molecule mimicry hunting strategy in the imperial cone snail, Conus imperialis. Science Advances 7 (11): eabf 2704. https: // doi. org / 10.1126 / sciadv. abf 2704" type="journal article" year="2021">
Torres 
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FB73FB98C93BCA1A" box="[1258,1309,1078,1104]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">et al</emphasis>
. (2021)
</bibRefCitation>
in including 
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD205A09FEC0FBF5CE3DCA39" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[345,539,1114,1140]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="genuanus">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FEC0FBF5CE3DCA39" box="[345,539,1114,1140]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Conus genuanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD205A09FDD8FBF5CF7DCA3E" authority="" authorityName="Morch" authorityYear="1852" box="[577,859,1113,1140]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Stephanoconus">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FDD8FBF5CEAACA3E" box="[577,652,1114,1140]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Conus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FD04FBF6CF69CA39" box="[669,847,1113,1139]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Stephanoconus</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="663E369ADD205A09FF7AFB35CF49CB54" blockId="34.[227,1437,1178,1310]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
Another point to investigate is the close phylogenetic relationship between 
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD205A09FB19FB34CE33CA92" authority="Linnaeus, 1758" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="genuanus" subGenus="Stephanoconus">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FB19FB34C8EDCAFF" box="[1152,1227,1179,1205]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Conus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FB78FB35C9B5CAFE" box="[1249,1427,1178,1204]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Stephanoconus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FF7AFB11CD75CA9D" box="[227,339,1214,1239]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">genuanus</emphasis>
Linnaeus, 1758
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD205A09FDCAFB11C85CCA92" authority="Azuma, 1972" authorityName="Azuma" authorityYear="1972" box="[595,1146,1214,1240]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="chiangi" subGenus="Stephanoconus">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FDCAFB11CEB8CA92" box="[595,670,1214,1240]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Conus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FD28FB11CF45CA92" box="[689,867,1214,1240]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Stephanoconus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FCEEFB11CFE9CA92" box="[887,975,1214,1240]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">chiangi</emphasis>
Azuma, 1972
</taxonomicName>
, an Indo-Pacific species (
<bibRefCitation id="02104B6BDD205A09FF72FB4ECDBACAB1" author="Lin Z. &amp; Torres J. P. &amp; Watkins M. &amp; Paguigan N. &amp; Niu C. &amp; Imperial J. S. &amp; Tun J. &amp; Safavi-Hemami H. &amp; Urdaneta R. K. &amp; Neves J. L. B. &amp; Espino S. &amp; Karthikeyan M. &amp; Olivera B. M. &amp; Schmidt E. W." box="[235,412,1249,1275]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="685" refId="ref30563" refString="Lin Z., Torres J. P., Watkins M., Paguigan N., Niu C., Imperial J. S., Tun J., Safavi-Hemami H., Finol- Urdaneta R. K., Neves J. L. B., Espino S., Karthikeyan M., Olivera B. M. &amp; Schmidt E. W. 2021. Nonpeptidic small molecule components from cone snail venoms. Frontiers in Pharmacology 12: 685. https: // doi. org / 10.3389 / fphar. 2021.655981" type="journal article" year="2021">
Lin 
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FE85FB4DCD69CAB1" box="[284,335,1249,1275]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">et al</emphasis>
. 2021
</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 2). Their phylogenetic proximity evidently points towards the closure of the Tethys Ocean, acting as a barrier and isolating the populations.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="663E369ADD205A09FF7AFAE9C8F2C832" blockId="34.[227,1437,1349,1657]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
In 
<bibRefCitation id="02104B6BDD205A09FE9AFAE9CDD5CB15" author="Psarras C. &amp; Koskeridou E. &amp; Merle D." box="[259,499,1349,1376]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="1309 - 1339" refId="ref31391" refString="Psarras C., Koskeridou E. &amp; Merle D. 2021. Late Miocene Conidae (Mollusca: Gastropoda) of Crete (Greece). Part 1: genera Conilithes and Conus (Kalloconus). Geodiversitas 43 (24): 1309 - 1339. https: // doi. org / 10.5252 / geodiversitas 2021 v 43 a 24" type="journal article" year="2021">
Psarras 
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FEC6FAE9CDB5CB15" box="[351,403,1349,1375]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">et al</emphasis>
. (2021)
</bibRefCitation>
, we considered that 
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD205A09FD7AFAE9CD51CBC8" authority="Psarras, Koskeridou &amp; Merle, 2021" authorityName="Psarras, Koskeridou &amp; Merle" authorityYear="2021" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="asterousiaensis" subGenus="Kalloconus">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FD7AFAE9CF08CB2A" box="[739,814,1350,1376]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Conus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FCA6FAEACFE3CB15" box="[831,965,1349,1375]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Kalloconus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FC4FFAE9C8ACCB15" box="[982,1162,1350,1375]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">asterousiaensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="02104B6BDD205A09FB08FAE9CD51CBC8" author="Psarras C. &amp; Koskeridou E. &amp; Merle D." pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="1309 - 1339" refId="ref31391" refString="Psarras C., Koskeridou E. &amp; Merle D. 2021. Late Miocene Conidae (Mollusca: Gastropoda) of Crete (Greece). Part 1: genera Conilithes and Conus (Kalloconus). Geodiversitas 43 (24): 1309 - 1339. https: // doi. org / 10.5252 / geodiversitas 2021 v 43 a 24" type="journal article" year="2021">Psarras, Koskeridou &amp; Merle, 2021</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD205A09FDF9FAC6CF01CBC8" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[608,807,1385,1411]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="genuanus">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FDF9FAC6CF01CBC8" box="[608,807,1385,1411]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Conus genuanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, both in morphology and colour pattern variations. The characters used to assign 
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD205A09FDD6FA23CF71CBEF" authorityName="Psarras, Koskeridou &amp; Merle" authorityYear="2021" box="[591,855,1420,1446]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="asterousiaensis">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FDD6FA23CF71CBEF" box="[591,855,1420,1446]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Conus asterousiaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD205A09FC1BFA23C856CBEC" authority="" authorityName="da Motta" authorityYear="1991" box="[898,1136,1419,1446]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Kalloconus">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FC1BFA23CFEBCBEC" box="[898,973,1420,1446]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Conus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FC78FA24C841CBEF" box="[993,1127,1419,1445]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Kalloconus</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
were the morphology of the conical smooth spire and the multispiral protoconch. This subgeneric attribution was done, but before the phylogenetic works of 
<bibRefCitation id="02104B6BDD205A09FDF2FA7DCF0ECBA6" author="Lin Z. &amp; Torres J. P. &amp; Watkins M. &amp; Paguigan N. &amp; Niu C. &amp; Imperial J. S. &amp; Tun J. &amp; Safavi-Hemami H. &amp; Urdaneta R. K. &amp; Neves J. L. B. &amp; Espino S. &amp; Karthikeyan M. &amp; Olivera B. M. &amp; Schmidt E. W." box="[619,808,1490,1516]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="685" refId="ref30563" refString="Lin Z., Torres J. P., Watkins M., Paguigan N., Niu C., Imperial J. S., Tun J., Safavi-Hemami H., Finol- Urdaneta R. K., Neves J. L. B., Espino S., Karthikeyan M., Olivera B. M. &amp; Schmidt E. W. 2021. Nonpeptidic small molecule components from cone snail venoms. Frontiers in Pharmacology 12: 685. https: // doi. org / 10.3389 / fphar. 2021.655981" type="journal article" year="2021">
Lin 
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FD03FA7DCEF3CBA6" box="[666,725,1490,1516]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">et al.</emphasis>
(2021)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="02104B6BDD205A09FCF9FA7DC867CBA6" author="Torres J. P. &amp; Lin Z. &amp; Watkins M. &amp; Salcedo P. F. &amp; Baskin R. P. &amp; Elhabian S. &amp; Safavi-Hemami H. &amp; Taylor D. &amp; Tun J. &amp; Concepcion G. P. &amp; Saguil N. &amp; Yanagihara A. A. &amp; Fang Y. &amp; McArthur J. R. &amp; Tae H. - S. &amp; Finol-Urdaneta R. K. &amp; Ozpolat B. D. &amp; Olivera B. M. &amp; Schmidt E. W." box="[864,1089,1490,1516]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="2704" refId="ref32225" refString="Torres J. P., Lin Z., Watkins M., Salcedo P. F., Baskin R. P., Elhabian S., Safavi-Hemami H., Taylor D., Tun J., Concepcion G. P., Saguil N., Yanagihara A. A., Fang Y., McArthur J. R., Tae H. - S., Finol-Urdaneta R. K., Ozpolat B. D., Olivera B. M. &amp; Schmidt E. W. 2021. Small-molecule mimicry hunting strategy in the imperial cone snail, Conus imperialis. Science Advances 7 (11): eabf 2704. https: // doi. org / 10.1126 / sciadv. abf 2704" type="journal article" year="2021">
Torres 
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FC28FA7DCFC2CBA6" box="[945,996,1490,1516]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">et al</emphasis>
. (2021)
</bibRefCitation>
became available, and 
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD205A09FAC8FA7DCE05C845" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="genuanus" subGenus="Stephanoconus">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FAC8FA7DC9BACBA6" box="[1361,1436,1490,1516]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Conus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FF74FA5ACDB9C845" box="[237,415,1525,1551]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Stephanoconus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FE2AFA59CE05C845" box="[435,547,1526,1551]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">genuanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has previously been included in other subgenera (e.g., in 
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FB69FA5AC950C845" box="[1264,1398,1525,1551]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Kalloconus</emphasis>
da 
<bibRefCitation id="02104B6BDD205A09FF7AF9B7CD52C878" author="Motta A. J. D. da" box="[227,372,1560,1586]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" refId="ref31120" refString="Motta A. J. D. da 1991. A Systematic Classification of the Gastropod Family Conidae at the Generic Level. La Conchiglia, Ludwigsburg." type="book" year="1991">Motta, 1991</bibRefCitation>
by da 
<bibRefCitation id="02104B6BDD205A09FE5EF9B7CE43C878" author="Motta A. J. D. da" box="[455,613,1560,1586]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" refId="ref31120" refString="Motta A. J. D. da 1991. A Systematic Classification of the Gastropod Family Conidae at the Generic Level. La Conchiglia, Ludwigsburg." type="book" year="1991">Motta (1991)</bibRefCitation>
and in 
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD205A09FD5BF9B7C8BFC878" authority="Tucker &amp; Tenorio, 2009" authorityName="Tucker &amp; Tenorio" authorityYear="2009" box="[706,1177,1560,1586]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Genuanoconus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FD5BF9B7CF54C878" box="[706,882,1560,1586]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Genuanoconus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="02104B6BDD205A09FCE0F9B7C8BFC878" author="Tucker J. K. &amp; Tenorio M. J." box="[889,1177,1560,1586]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" refId="ref32426" refString="Tucker J. K. &amp; Tenorio M. J. 2009. Systematic Classification of Recent and Fossil Conoidean Gastropods: With Keys to the Genera of Cone Shells. ConchBooks, Harxheim." type="book" year="2009">Tucker &amp; Tenorio, 2009</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="02104B6BDD205A09FB5EF9B7CD19C81F" author="Tucker J. K. &amp; Tenorio M. J." pageId="34" pageNumber="35" refId="ref32426" refString="Tucker J. K. &amp; Tenorio M. J. 2009. Systematic Classification of Recent and Fossil Conoidean Gastropods: With Keys to the Genera of Cone Shells. ConchBooks, Harxheim." type="book" year="2009">Tucker &amp; Tenorio (2009))</bibRefCitation>
. The colour pattern of 
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD205A09FDFEF994CF55C81F" authorityName="Psarras, Koskeridou &amp; Merle" authorityYear="2021" box="[615,883,1595,1621]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="asterousiaensis">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FDFEF994CF55C81F" box="[615,883,1595,1621]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Conus asterousiaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to that of most species of 
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD205A09FAC8F994CD8FC833" authority="" authorityName="Morch" authorityYear="1852" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Stephanoconus">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FAC8F994C9BAC81F" box="[1361,1436,1595,1621]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Conus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FF74F9F1CDB9C832" box="[237,415,1630,1656]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Stephanoconus</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
, prompting us to consider it as a member of 
<taxonomicName id="A1814D19DD205A09FC2CF9F1C8EBC833" authority="" authorityName="Morch" authorityYear="1852" box="[949,1229,1630,1657]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Stephanoconus">
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FC2CF9F1C826C832" box="[949,1024,1630,1656]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Conus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="54F5EA88DD205A09FB88F9F1C8E5C832" box="[1041,1219,1630,1656]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Stephanoconus</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
